index (P < 0.001). Significant difference was confirmed between incidences for 
disease based on the results of OGTT and glycated haemoglobin test when two 
different criteria systems were used. Age was the strongest predictor of 
pre-diabetes/diabetes (P = 0.016). The presence of metabolic syndrome increased 
the level of glycated haemoglobin by an average of 0.2% in normal glycemic 
status.

